(Directed by Liu Xue Song)

3
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:37,079
(Episode 6)

4
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,079
I have my first love

5
00:01:41,799 --> 00:01:44,760
Maybe I have a first love

6
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,680
My gosh.

7
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:50,400
Sir,

8
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:52,920
this Boston lobster is the restaurant's specialty.

9
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:53,959
We have a promotion today.

10
00:01:53,959 --> 00:01:55,719
It's only 499 yuan each.

11
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,599
Would you like to try it?

12
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,200
Yes.

13
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,439
Well...

14
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:07,239
We lived in Boston for quite a bit.

15
00:02:07,239 --> 00:02:08,370
I'll pass for today.

16
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,370
Okay? I'm tired of eating it.

17
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,879
Just go with what I said...

18
00:02:15,090 --> 00:02:16,090
You're here.

19
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:20,719
Thank you.

20
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,879
Lighting up white candles in broad daylight.

21
00:02:27,090 --> 00:02:28,560
Who are you commemorating?

22
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:32,439
To celebrate our beautiful day.

23
00:02:34,199 --> 00:02:35,199
Excuse me.

24
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,560
- We... - We're here.

25
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,439
What...

26
00:02:39,439 --> 00:02:40,599
Let me introduce you.

27
00:02:40,599 --> 00:02:41,810
They are my two good friends.

28
00:02:41,810 --> 00:02:43,319
Xiao Hong and Yuan Yuan.

29
00:02:43,919 --> 00:02:46,960
He's the handsome man who's treating us today.

30
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,080
Hai Xing.

31
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:51,039
I don't think he's buying us dinner.

32
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,280
There are only two sets of utensils.

33
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,000
No.

34
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,360
No such thing.

35
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,840
Prepare more utensils.

36
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,599
- Can't you see we have more people? - Yes, sir.

37
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,639
I'm sorry. Is it Hong Hong?

38
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:03,120
Xiao Yuan.

39
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:05,080
I'm Hai Xing.

40
00:03:05,439 --> 00:03:07,120
Hai as in the ocean.

41
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,400
Xing as in the stars.

42
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,439
What would you guys like to eat?

43
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:13,919
Have you eaten?

44
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,960
Who would come to the restaurant after eating?

45
00:03:16,719 --> 00:03:18,520
I just finished my training.

46
00:03:18,719 --> 00:03:20,639
My team was saying they were famished.

47
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:23,199
Initially, I was going to invite them to come too.

48
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,240
But I didn't want you to spend too much money.

49
00:03:25,479 --> 00:03:27,199
So I only asked my best friends to come over.

50
00:03:28,879 --> 00:03:29,919
Okay.

51
00:03:32,039 --> 00:03:33,960
I already ordered something.

52
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:36,680
You ladies are welcome to add more.

53
00:03:36,879 --> 00:03:38,080
I was waiting for you to say that.

54
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,520
- Excuse me. - Yes?

55
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,120
What did the man just order?

56
00:03:41,319 --> 00:03:43,080
- Well... - Actually, I think...

57
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:44,960
- One Caesar salad. - Yes.

58
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,360
Two spaghetti Bolognese.

59
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,439
That's it?

60
00:03:47,639 --> 00:03:49,719
That's all? It's not enough.

61
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:51,000
We'll have a Boston lobster too.

62
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,560
I want to eat abalone.

63
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,759
You two really know me well.

64
00:03:55,759 --> 00:03:57,080
Those are all my favorites.

65
00:04:01,439 --> 00:04:02,520
Let's add that.

66
00:04:03,039 --> 00:04:04,360
- Add that. - Okay.

67
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,610
Don't you need anything else?

68
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:24,610
I ate a lot for lunch.

69
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:26,480
So I won't eat so much for dinner.

70
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,480
I'm okay.

71
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,610
I'll just watch you ladies eat.

72
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:43,279
Goodness me.

73
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:44,959
The food here is pretty good.

74
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:47,000
How did you find this place?

75
00:04:47,279 --> 00:04:48,610
I found it online.

76
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,279
I've been wanting to try it.

77
00:04:50,279 --> 00:04:52,399
I was wondering who I could get to pay for the meal.

78
00:04:52,399 --> 00:04:54,759
It just so happens someone offered.

79
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,560
Hai Xing, you're so lucky.

80
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,170
You should change your name to Lucky Star.

81
00:05:02,399 --> 00:05:03,800
Don't just eat. Let's drink.

82
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,480
- Cheers. - Cheers.

83
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:06,839
To happiness.

84
00:05:06,839 --> 00:05:07,839
- Yes, to happiness. - Please.

85
00:05:07,839 --> 00:05:08,959
- Thank you. - Thank you.

86
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:10,079
You're welcome.

87
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:14,610
It's good.

88
00:05:14,839 --> 00:05:15,879
Try this, Qian Qian.

89
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,000
All right.

90
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,920
I'm going to get more water.

91
00:05:19,730 --> 00:05:20,730
Eat up.

92
00:05:21,050 --> 00:05:22,170
Here. Aren't these abalones for you?

93
00:05:22,170 --> 00:05:23,480
I like this one.

94
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:25,079
Trust me, it's delicious.

95
00:05:25,079 --> 00:05:26,240
- Miss. - It's so good.

96
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,519
Take a picture.

97
00:05:28,319 --> 00:05:29,319
What are you doing?

98
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,319
Can you stop gossiping?

99
00:05:32,319 --> 00:05:33,319
I'll stop.

100
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:41,839
Miss, what's our total bill?

101
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,279
Hold on. I'll check.

102
00:05:44,279 --> 00:05:45,319
All right. Thank you.

103
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,600
There's so much meat.

104
00:05:51,759 --> 00:05:52,839
Hello.

105
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:55,120
The total is 1,888 yuan.

106
00:05:55,759 --> 00:05:57,000
When can we eat this again?

107
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,240
I don't know.

108
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,720
Well...

109
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:10,720
I'm in the food business too.

110
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,160
We're a family.

111
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,920
What about a bit of a discount?

112
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,120
Look.

113
00:06:17,519 --> 00:06:18,759
What about 1,500 yuan?

114
00:06:19,319 --> 00:06:22,079
It's okay. That lady already paid for it.

115
00:06:27,879 --> 00:06:29,519
Listen, you two. Eat up.

116
00:06:29,519 --> 00:06:31,240
You won't be able to eat it if you pack it up. Okay?

117
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,279
- No need to pack. - No need.

118
00:06:32,279 --> 00:06:34,000
- We'll eat it here. - We'll finish it here.

119
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,560
It's fine even if I gain 10kg.

120
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,560
Indeed.

121
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,680
Get me one of those.

122
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,519
- The salmon. - Eat more fruits.

123
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,800
It's so good.

124
00:06:45,199 --> 00:06:46,199
It's good, right?

125
00:06:46,199 --> 00:06:47,600
It's better than my mom's.

126
00:06:48,079 --> 00:06:49,959
This is embarrassing.

127
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:52,160
The man should be the one paying when eating out.

128
00:06:52,319 --> 00:06:53,399
I'll pay next time, okay?

129
00:06:53,399 --> 00:06:54,439
Next time, it's on me.

130
00:06:54,439 --> 00:06:55,959
It's fine. No need to be so polite.

131
00:06:55,959 --> 00:06:57,480
If you're really sincere about it,

132
00:06:57,759 --> 00:07:00,399
I'll call my whole team and you can foot the bill.

133
00:07:00,839 --> 00:07:02,240
Listen, Qian Qian, I think...

134
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,240
it's fine if it's just the two of us.

135
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,360
Do I have to spell it out for you?

136
00:07:07,079 --> 00:07:08,920
No, I get what you mean.

137
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,800
It's normal that you don't feel the same way about me now.

138
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,319
But I think when it comes to relationships,

139
00:07:12,319 --> 00:07:13,399
as long as one party is interested,

140
00:07:13,399 --> 00:07:14,600
it's halfway to success.

141
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,800
So you go with logic.

142
00:07:15,959 --> 00:07:17,319
I think "halfway" is putting it lightly.

143
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:19,000
There's no way you don't have any feelings for me.

144
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,360
Otherwise, why did you pay for me?

145
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:22,399
Don't you think we are completely different?

146
00:07:22,639 --> 00:07:23,800
So we complement each other.

147
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,800
It should be celebrated.

148
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:25,839
Goodbye.

149
00:07:25,839 --> 00:07:26,920
I'll see you tomorrow, okay?

150
00:07:27,439 --> 00:07:28,439
Drive slowly.

151
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,240
Buckle up.

152
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,639
And you ladies...

153
00:07:38,759 --> 00:07:39,759
She's so cool.

154
00:07:42,399 --> 00:07:43,399
Actually,

155
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,240
I didn't want to say it directly.

156
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,800
But I realized that...

157
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,439
if I didn't tell him directly, he'd never understood.

158
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,519
It's better this way.

159
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,000
That will make him realize...

160
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,920
that it won't work out between us.

161
00:07:56,319 --> 00:07:57,720
Are you sure you made that clear?

162
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,279
I made it very clear.

163
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:02,480
That's good. No need to make things more awkward.

164
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,240
You're much better than me.

165
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,800
Right?

166
00:08:08,439 --> 00:08:10,160
No one has paid for me before.

167
00:08:10,639 --> 00:08:12,160
What does that tell you?

168
00:08:12,439 --> 00:08:14,879
She paid close to 2,000 yuan.

169
00:08:16,319 --> 00:08:17,600
A girl spent money on a boy.

170
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,360
What does that tell you? Right?

171
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,480
She even brought her friends.

172
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,879
If you put it like that,

173
00:08:23,839 --> 00:08:24,839
then it's a success.

174
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,600
You could certainly say that.

175
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:28,959
But it's just that I'm still a little reserved.

176
00:08:29,079 --> 00:08:30,079
But I understand.

177
00:08:30,199 --> 00:08:31,759
I've seen those romantic shows.

178
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,330
When the woman is reserved,

179
00:08:33,639 --> 00:08:35,399
the man has to be determined.

180
00:08:35,759 --> 00:08:37,240
Don't worry. This matter...

181
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,679
You can send me your blessings.

182
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:40,679
Okay.

183
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,559
Good night. I wish you happiness.

184
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,039
You're such a brag.

185
00:08:50,450 --> 00:08:51,519
Hey.

186
00:08:52,559 --> 00:08:54,210
There's something going on between Hai Xing and Qian Qian.

187
00:08:54,330 --> 00:08:55,360
What?

188
00:08:55,919 --> 00:08:57,159
Hai Xing called me.

189
00:08:57,330 --> 00:08:58,600
He said Qian Qian is interested in him.

190
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,279
I think they can make it.

191
00:09:00,279 --> 00:09:01,279
That's not it.

192
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:02,399
Tell him.

193
00:09:02,519 --> 00:09:03,720
Hai Xing misunderstood.

194
00:09:04,279 --> 00:09:05,360
I'm hanging up.

195
00:09:07,759 --> 00:09:08,759
You heard her.

196
00:09:08,759 --> 00:09:10,039
She must be embarrassed.

197
00:09:10,679 --> 00:09:12,279
Hai Xing told me that...

198
00:09:12,559 --> 00:09:15,240
Qian Qian is trying to play hard to get.

199
00:09:15,559 --> 00:09:17,600
Hai Xing sees right through it.

200
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,960
He's totally taking on the challenge.

201
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,799
Maybe Hai Xing got the wrong idea.

202
00:09:22,799 --> 00:09:23,919
Don't worry about him.

203
00:09:33,799 --> 00:09:35,450
As for the Haicheng No. 8 project,

204
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:36,720
we finally secured it.

205
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,840
It's going to be a tough road ahead.

206
00:09:39,210 --> 00:09:40,210
Hou Jue,

207
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,639
you will lead the execution plan.

208
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:44,519
Sure.

209
00:09:44,639 --> 00:09:47,000
I think I should work with Bao Xiao Han.

210
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,159
The two of us will make a more comprehensive team.

211
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:52,039
Mr. Hou Junior, thank you for thinking highly of me.

212
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:53,960
But I don't think I'm able to do it.

213
00:09:54,330 --> 00:09:56,279
Why? Haven't you done it before?

214
00:09:56,639 --> 00:09:59,240
I've only handled small projects.

215
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,600
They're very small ones.

216
00:10:00,919 --> 00:10:02,210
This one is not that big.

217
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:05,000
But Zhirong Construction has a very high standard.

218
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,559
- I really can't. - All right.

219
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:10,000
You should be ashamed for not stepping up to the plate.

220
00:10:11,399 --> 00:10:13,360
Since Bao Xiao Han won't take it,

221
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,519
you do it yourself.

222
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:17,330
Come up with an idea next Monday.

223
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:21,360
This is the best opportunity for you to prove yourself to the company.

224
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:23,330
Meeting adjourned.

225
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,039
I win.

226
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:41,360
What the heck?

227
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,559
Why is my luck getting worse?

228
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,519
I can't seem to win.

229
00:10:45,799 --> 00:10:48,210
Why don't we call it a day?

230
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:51,330
Tie Hao is out of money anyway.

231
00:10:51,330 --> 00:10:52,360
What do you mean?

232
00:10:52,679 --> 00:10:53,840
Are you calling me broke now?

233
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,360
That's not it.

234
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,559
You're afraid that I won't pay, right?

235
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,039
Don't worry.

236
00:10:58,679 --> 00:11:00,679
Your brother has an ATM, okay?

237
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,039
Where's the ATM?

238
00:11:03,919 --> 00:11:05,919
Where? Do you think I'm going to tell you?

239
00:11:07,759 --> 00:11:09,399
Come now. Tie Hao never owed us money.

240
00:11:09,399 --> 00:11:10,399
Come on.

241
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,360
When are we going to do it?

242
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:19,000
It's off.

243
00:11:21,759 --> 00:11:22,919
What's happening?

244
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,039
Let me make a call.

245
00:11:51,279 --> 00:11:52,960
My cousin, don't do this.

246
